  "text": "Our data showed that contact with cats in the last 12 months may be protective against asthma in the first year of life. This is in agreement with previous studies [CITATION_1] . A potential mechanism was proposed by PlattsMills et al. who indicated that contact with cats could induce IgG and IgG4 antibody responses, which is protective against the development of asthma [CITATION_2] .",
